begin_memory_text: where we live. New Mexico, Ohio. What is our covid working situation
middle_memory_text: mostly about cats - cats and more cats. It was great!
rest_of_day_open: I have things to do this weekend - a small household project to complete. Plus I have a yoga class and want to meet a friend for a hike. Then it's back to work (virtually) on Monday. Same old same old, right? So no big stresses, just the usual household routine
critical_positive: we found common ground in cats for sure. This guy has 13 of them or something! and I got to see 2 of them closeup. That just made the conversation for me. And basically anything we threw out at each other seemed to engender a dialog. It was cool he's from NM where I had spent time earlier this century

begin_memory_text: The start was simply discussing what we were doing and why--just hypothesizing why the study was taking place and what researchers are trying to learn.  This followed by where we were located and what we did in life.
middle_memory_text:
The majority of the conversation was focused on location and language--slang and all.  How terminology is fun to learn about and the differences.  Then a couple of my cats showed up and steered the conversation toward animal life and care.
Back to location and travel summed it all up.
end_memory_text:
The conclusion was getting wrapped up quick--but she had brought up a question which would have taken a while to unwrap.  I tried to answer it fully enough, but it ended oddly.

We seemed to recover by summing up that it was a fine conversation and thanking each other for the time spent.
rest_of_day_open: After having the wife home after her break--and both of us relaxing and completing household chores, it's actually back to basics for both of us.  Typical for a usual week; working on and accomplishing our own goals and anything new that pops up during the time.  Relaxation and hobbies during our down time to keep us sane as well.
critical_positive: I believe the paramount thing that attributed to the conversation was our seemingly similar interests, mindset and curiosity on life events and occasions, and the idea of not dominating the conversation.  We both were able to share an idea and then explain ourselves without the other interrupting or taking over.
critical_negative: There were only a few brief moments where the silent pauses indicated we both did not know where to lead to next--very minor though.  I am also an uncomfortable person speaking with strangers and most likely fidgeted and stuttered quite a bit--probably throwing her off perhaps.  Her camera positioning was a minor influence; but that would be a personal factor.
